Because our 2021 quantitative analyses included all of our reporting units, the summation of our reporting units&#8217; fair values, as indicated by our discounted cash flow calculations, were compared to our consolidated fair value, as indicated by our market capitalization, to evaluate the reasonableness of our calculations. This impairment assessment is sensitive to changes in forecasted cash flows, as well as our selected discount rate. Changes in the reporting unit&#8217;s results, forecast assumptions and estimates could materially affect the estimation of the fair value of the reporting units.

